<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 18 at 1:34AM EST  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A LINE OF GUSTY SHOWERS WILL AFFECT EASTERN
ROCKINGHAM...CASWELL...SOUTH CENTRAL APPOMATTOX...
CHARLOTTE...SOUTHEASTERN CAMPBELL...EASTERN PITTSYLVANIA AND HALIFAX
COUNTIES AND THE CITY OF DANVILLE...
At 132 AM EST, radar indicated showers were located along a line
extending from near Spring Mills to Bethany. Movement was east at 60
mph.
Winds in excess of 40 mph are possible with these showers.
Locations impacted include...
Danville...
Eden...
Reidsville...
South Boston...
Wentworth...
Yanceyville...
and Bethel.
Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</description>
